In a world where dogs run wild and free,
Cats sit and watch, sipping their tea.
With fur so soft, and eyes like the stars,
They ponder the antics of their canine counterparts.

Dogs chase after sticks with boundless cheer,
While cats perch calmly, their vision so clear.
Each bark of a puppy, a curious song,
To the feline audience, who silently throng.

In gardens of dreams where the sunflowers sway,
Both find their joy in their own special way.
Cats might just smirk, with a flick of their tail,
As dogs wag their pride, their happiness unveiled.

So here’s to the cats, on the dogs' branch they sit,
Observing the world, every prank and every wit.
Though different in ways, they share the same space,
In a playground of paws, a harmonious grace.
